						<summary>

						<p>On a rock on the hill outside the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">10th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to the <hi rend="italic">nishidhika</hi> of the jaina ascetic Pushpaṇandi and records the death [by Sallekhana] of the <hi rend="italic">muni</hi> Purimaṇḍala, a disciple of Pushapaṇandi <hi rend="italic">muni.</hi> Two small lines on the right side are indistinct.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 10th century A.D. </p>						

						</summary>
